d 'ASYCAUS': module to provide Asymmetric Granger-Causality Suite 
d
d	asycaus implements the full battery of asymmetric Granger
d causality tests for time    series. Each subcommand decomposes
d the two series into cumulative positive and cumulative   
d negative shocks following Granger and Yoon (2002), then conducts
d the relevant inference    within an augmented VAR (Toda and
d Yamamoto 1995).    The package is bivariate by design (testing
d whether causvar causes depvar) and follows	Hatemi-J's program
d — the inference is exact when combined with the leverage
d bootstrap    (Hacker and Hatemi-J, 2006, 2012). The default
d lag-selection criterion is the Hatemi-J    information criterion
d (HJC; Hatemi-J 2003), with AIC, AICC, SBC and HQC also available 
d   via ic().	 For each subcommand a professional table is
d printed and a publication-quality graph is	produced (suppress
d with nograph). 
d
d KW: Granger causality
d KW: asymmetry
d KW: time series
d
d Requires: Stata version 14 
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260719
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f asycaus.ado
f asycaus.sthlp
f asycaus_all.ado
f asycaus_dynamic.ado
f asycaus_efficient.ado
f asycaus_fourier.ado
f asycaus_quantile.ado
f asycaus_spectral.ado
f asycaus_static.ado
f asycaus_engine.mata
f ../_/_asycaus_check_tsset.ado
f asycaus_engine.mata
f ../_/_asycaus_footer.ado
f ../_/_asycaus_header.ado
f ../_/_asycaus_iccode.ado
f asycaus_all.sthlp
f asycaus_dynamic.sthlp
f asycaus_efficient.sthlp
f asycaus_fourier.sthlp
f asycaus_quantile.sthlp
f asycaus_spectral.sthlp
f asycaus_static.sthlp
